{"section": "Exercise 3.17.1: Devising recursive definitions for sets of strings.", "qid": 0, "instructions": "<div class=\"setup\">\n <p>\n  Let A = {a, b}.\n </p>\n</div>\n", "input_type": null, "question": "<div class=\"question\">\n <span class=\"part\">\n  (a)\n </span>\n <div class=\"text\">\n  <p>\n   Give a recursive definition for A\n   <sup>\n    *\n   </sup>\n   .\n  </p>\n </div>\n</div>\n", "choices": [], "correct_choice_index": null, "answer": "<div class=\"answer\">\n <ul>\n  <li>\n   Base case:  \u03bb \u2208 A\n   <sup>\n    *\n   </sup>\n  </li>\n  <li>\n   Recursive rule: if x \u2208 A\n   <sup>\n    *\n   </sup>\n   then,\n   <br/>\n   <br/>\n   <ul>\n    <li>\n     xa \u2208 A\n     <sup>\n      *\n     </sup>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n     xb \u2208 A\n     <sup>\n      *\n     </sup>\n    </li>\n   </ul>\n  </li>\n </ul>\n</div>\n", "explanation": null, "images": {"instructions": "3.17.1-exercise-instructions_div.png", "question": "3.17.1.0-exercise-question.png", "choices": []}}